19static constexpr bool kNeedI64RegPair = kSystemPointerSize == 4;
20static constexpr bool kNeedS128RegPair = kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine;
21
22enum RegClass : uint8_t {
23 kGpReg,
24 kFpReg,
25 kGpRegPair = kFpReg + 1 + (kNeedS128RegPair && !kNeedI64RegPair),
26 kFpRegPair = kFpReg + 1 + kNeedI64RegPair,
27 kNoReg = kFpRegPair + kNeedS128RegPair,
28 // +------------------+-------------------------------+
29 // | | kNeedI64RegPair |
30 // +------------------+---------------+---------------+
31 // | kNeedS128RegPair | true | false |
32 // +------------------+---------------+---------------+
33 // | true | 0,1,2,3,4 (a) | 0,1,3,2,3 |
34 // | false | 0,1,2,3,3 (b) | 0,1,2,2,2 (c) |
35 // +------------------+---------------+---------------+
36 // (a) arm
37 // (b) ia32
38 // (c) x64, arm64
39};
40
41static_assert(kNeedI64RegPair == (kGpRegPair != kNoReg),
42 "kGpRegPair equals kNoReg if unused");
43static_assert(kNeedS128RegPair == (kFpRegPair != kNoReg),
44 "kFpRegPair equals kNoReg if unused");
45
46enum RegPairHalf : uint8_t { kLowWord = 0, kHighWord = 1 };
47
48static inline constexpr bool needs_gp_reg_pair(ValueKind kind) {
49 return kNeedI64RegPair && kind == kI64;
50}
51
52static inline constexpr bool needs_fp_reg_pair(ValueKind kind) {
53 return kNeedS128RegPair && kind == kS128;
54}
55
56static inline constexpr RegClass reg_class_for(ValueKind kind) {
57 // Statically generate an array that we use for lookup at runtime.
58 constexpr size_t kNumValueKinds = static_cast<size_t>(kBottom);
59 constexpr auto kRegClasses =
60 base::make_array<kNumValueKinds>([](std::size_t kind) {
61 switch (kind) {
62 case kF32:
63 case kF64:
64 return kFpReg;
65 case kI8:
66 case kI16:
67 case kI32:
68 return kGpReg;
69 case kI64:
70 return kNeedI64RegPair ? kGpRegPair : kGpReg;
71 case kS128:
72 return kNeedS128RegPair ? kFpRegPair : kFpReg;
73 case kRef:
74 case kRefNull:
75 case kRtt:
76 return kGpReg;
77 case kVoid:
78 return kNoReg; // unsupported kind
79 }
80 CONSTEXPR_UNREACHABLE();
81 });
82 V8_ASSUME(kind < kNumValueKinds);
83 RegClass rc = kRegClasses[kind];
84 V8_ASSUME(rc != kNoReg);
85 return rc;
86}
87
88// Description of LiftoffRegister code encoding.
89// This example uses the ARM architecture, which as of writing has:
90// - 9 GP registers, requiring 4 bits
91// - 13 FP registers, requiring 5 bits
92// - kNeedI64RegPair is true
93// - kNeedS128RegPair is true
94// - thus, kBitsPerRegPair is 2 + 2 * 4 = 10
95// - storage_t is uint16_t
96// The table below illustrates how each RegClass is encoded, with brackets
97// surrounding the bits which encode the register number.
98//
99// +----------------+------------------+
100// | RegClass | Example |
101// +----------------+------------------+
102// | kGpReg (1) | [00 0000 0000] |
103// | kFpReg (2) | [00 0000 1001] |
104// | kGpRegPair (3) | 01 [0000] [0001] |
105// | kFpRegPair (4) | 10 000[0 0010] |
106// +----------------+------------------+
107//
108// gp and fp registers are encoded in the same index space, which means that
109// code has to check for kGpRegPair and kFpRegPair before it can treat the code
110// as a register code.
111// (1) [0 .. kMaxGpRegCode] encodes gp registers
112// (2) [kMaxGpRegCode + 1 .. kMaxGpRegCode + kMaxFpRegCode] encodes fp
113// registers, so in this example, 1001 is really fp register 0.
114// (3) The second top bit is set for kGpRegPair, and the two gp registers are
115// stuffed side by side in code. Note that this is not the second top bit of
116// storage_t, since storage_t is larger than the number of meaningful bits we
117// need for the encoding.
118// (4) The top bit is set for kFpRegPair, and the fp register is stuffed into
119// the bottom part of the code. Unlike (2), this is the fp register code itself
120// (not sharing index space with gp), so in this example, it is fp register 2.
121
122// Maximum code of a gp cache register.
123static constexpr int kMaxGpRegCode = kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs.last().code();
124// Maximum code of an fp cache register.
125static constexpr int kMaxFpRegCode = kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.last().code();
126static constexpr int kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode = kMaxGpRegCode + 1;
127static constexpr int kAfterMaxLiftoffFpRegCode =
128 kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode + kMaxFpRegCode + 1;
129static constexpr int kAfterMaxLiftoffRegCode = kAfterMaxLiftoffFpRegCode;
130static constexpr int kBitsPerLiftoffRegCode =
131 32 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros<uint32_t>(kAfterMaxLiftoffRegCode - 1);
132static constexpr int kBitsPerGpRegCode =
133 32 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros<uint32_t>(kMaxGpRegCode);
134static constexpr int kBitsPerFpRegCode =
135 32 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros<uint32_t>(kMaxFpRegCode);
136// GpRegPair requires 1 extra bit, S128RegPair also needs an extra bit.
137static constexpr int kBitsPerRegPair =
138 (kNeedS128RegPair ? 2 : 1) + 2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode;
139
140static_assert(2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode >= kBitsPerFpRegCode,
141 "encoding for gp pair and fp pair collides");
142
143class LiftoffRegister {
144 static constexpr int needed_bits =
145 std::max(kNeedI64RegPair || kNeedS128RegPair ? kBitsPerRegPair : 0,
146 kBitsPerLiftoffRegCode);
147 using storage_t = std::conditional<
148 needed_bits <= 8, uint8_t,
149 std::conditional<needed_bits <= 16, uint16_t, uint32_t>::type>::type;
150
151 static_assert(8 * sizeof(storage_t) >= needed_bits,
152 "chosen type is big enough");
153 // Check for smallest required data type being chosen.
154 // Special case for uint8_t as there are no smaller types.
155 static_assert((8 * sizeof(storage_t) < 2 * needed_bits) ||
156 (sizeof(storage_t) == sizeof(uint8_t)),
157 "chosen type is small enough");
158
159 public:
160 constexpr explicit LiftoffRegister(Register reg)
161 : LiftoffRegister(reg.code()) {
162 DCHECK(kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs.has(reg));
163 DCHECK_EQ(reg, gp());
164 }
165 constexpr explicit LiftoffRegister(DoubleRegister reg)
166 : LiftoffRegister(kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode + reg.code()) {
167 DCHECK(kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.has(reg));
168 DCHECK_EQ(reg, fp());
169 }
170
171 static LiftoffRegister from_liftoff_code(int code) {
172 LiftoffRegister reg{static_cast<storage_t>(code)};
173 // Check that the code is correct by round-tripping through the
174 // reg-class-specific constructor.
175 DCHECK(
176 (reg.is_gp() && code == LiftoffRegister{reg.gp()}.liftoff_code()) ||
177 (reg.is_fp() && code == LiftoffRegister{reg.fp()}.liftoff_code()) ||
178 (reg.is_gp_pair() &&
179 code == ForPair(reg.low_gp(), reg.high_gp()).liftoff_code()) ||
180 (reg.is_fp_pair() && code == ForFpPair(reg.low_fp()).liftoff_code()));
181 return reg;
182 }
183
184 static LiftoffRegister from_code(RegClass rc, int code) {
185 switch (rc) {
186 case kGpReg:
187 return LiftoffRegister(Register::from_code(code));
188 case kFpReg:
189 return LiftoffRegister(DoubleRegister::from_code(code));
190 default:
191 UNREACHABLE();
192 }
193 }
194
195 // Shifts the register code depending on the type before converting to a
196 // LiftoffRegister.
197 static LiftoffRegister from_external_code(RegClass rc, ValueKind kind,
198 int code) {
199 if (kFPAliasing == AliasingKind::kCombine && kind == kF32) {
200 // Liftoff assumes a one-to-one mapping between float registers and
201 // double registers, and so does not distinguish between f32 and f64
202 // registers. The f32 register code must therefore be halved in order
203 // to pass the f64 code to Liftoff.
204 DCHECK_EQ(0, code % 2);
205 return LiftoffRegister::from_code(rc, code >> 1);
206 }
207 if (kNeedS128RegPair && kind == kS128) {
208 // Similarly for double registers and SIMD registers, the SIMD code
209 // needs to be doubled to pass the f64 code to Liftoff.
210 return LiftoffRegister::ForFpPair(DoubleRegister::from_code(code << 1));
211 }
212 return LiftoffRegister::from_code(rc, code);
213 }
214
215 static LiftoffRegister ForPair(Register low, Register high) {
216 DCHECK(kNeedI64RegPair);
217 DCHECK_NE(low, high);
218 storage_t combined_code = low.code() | (high.code() << kBitsPerGpRegCode) |
219 (1 << (2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode));
220 return LiftoffRegister(combined_code);
221 }
222
223 static LiftoffRegister ForFpPair(DoubleRegister low) {
224 DCHECK(kNeedS128RegPair);
225 DCHECK_EQ(0, low.code() % 2);
226 storage_t combined_code = low.code() | 2 << (2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode);
227 return LiftoffRegister(combined_code);
228 }
229
230 constexpr bool is_pair() const {
231 return (kNeedI64RegPair || kNeedS128RegPair) &&
232 (code_ & (3 << (2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode)));
233 }
234
235 constexpr bool is_gp_pair() const {
236 return kNeedI64RegPair && (code_ & (1 << (2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode))) != 0;
237 }
238 constexpr bool is_fp_pair() const {
239 return kNeedS128RegPair && (code_ & (2 << (2 * kBitsPerGpRegCode))) != 0;
240 }
241 constexpr bool is_gp() const { return code_ < kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode; }
242 constexpr bool is_fp() const {
243 return code_ >= kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode &&
244 code_ < kAfterMaxLiftoffFpRegCode;
245 }
246
247 LiftoffRegister low() const {
248 // Common case for most archs where only gp pair supported.
249 if (!kNeedS128RegPair) return LiftoffRegister(low_gp());
250 return is_gp_pair() ? LiftoffRegister(low_gp()) : LiftoffRegister(low_fp());
251 }
252
253 LiftoffRegister high() const {
254 // Common case for most archs where only gp pair supported.
255 if (!kNeedS128RegPair) return LiftoffRegister(high_gp());
256 return is_gp_pair() ? LiftoffRegister(high_gp())
257 : LiftoffRegister(high_fp());
258 }
259
260 Register low_gp() const {
261 DCHECK(is_gp_pair());
262 static constexpr storage_t kCodeMask = (1 << kBitsPerGpRegCode) - 1;
263 return Register::from_code(code_ & kCodeMask);
264 }
265
266 Register high_gp() const {
267 DCHECK(is_gp_pair());
268 static constexpr storage_t kCodeMask = (1 << kBitsPerGpRegCode) - 1;
269 return Register::from_code((code_ >> kBitsPerGpRegCode) & kCodeMask);
270 }
271
272 DoubleRegister low_fp() const {
273 DCHECK(is_fp_pair());
274 static constexpr storage_t kCodeMask = (1 << kBitsPerFpRegCode) - 1;
275 return DoubleRegister::from_code(code_ & kCodeMask);
276 }
277
278 DoubleRegister high_fp() const {
279 DCHECK(is_fp_pair());
280 static constexpr storage_t kCodeMask = (1 << kBitsPerFpRegCode) - 1;
281 return DoubleRegister::from_code((code_ & kCodeMask) + 1);
282 }
283
284 constexpr Register gp() const {
285 DCHECK(is_gp());
286 return Register::from_code(code_);
287 }
288
289 constexpr DoubleRegister fp() const {
290 DCHECK(is_fp());
291 return DoubleRegister::from_code(code_ - kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode);
292 }
293
294 constexpr int liftoff_code() const {
295 static_assert(sizeof(int) >= sizeof(storage_t));
296 return static_cast<int>(code_);
297 }
298
299 constexpr RegClass reg_class() const {
300 return is_fp_pair() ? kFpRegPair
301 : is_gp_pair() ? kGpRegPair : is_gp() ? kGpReg : kFpReg;
302 }
303
304 bool operator==(const LiftoffRegister other) const {
305 DCHECK_EQ(is_gp_pair(), other.is_gp_pair());
306 DCHECK_EQ(is_fp_pair(), other.is_fp_pair());
307 return code_ == other.code_;
308 }
309 bool operator!=(const LiftoffRegister other) const {
310 DCHECK_EQ(is_gp_pair(), other.is_gp_pair());
311 DCHECK_EQ(is_fp_pair(), other.is_fp_pair());
312 return code_ != other.code_;
313 }
314 bool overlaps(const LiftoffRegister other) const {
315 if (is_pair()) return low().overlaps(other) || high().overlaps(other);
316 if (other.is_pair()) return *this == other.low() || *this == other.high();
317 return *this == other;
318 }
319
320 private:
321 explicit constexpr LiftoffRegister(storage_t code) : code_(code) {}
322
323 storage_t code_;
324};
325ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(LiftoffRegister);
326
327inline std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, LiftoffRegister reg) {
328 if (reg.is_gp_pair()) {
329 return os << "<" << reg.low_gp() << "+" << reg.high_gp() << ">";
330 } else if (reg.is_fp_pair()) {
331 return os << "<" << reg.low_fp() << "+" << reg.high_fp() << ">";
332 } else if (reg.is_gp()) {
333 return os << reg.gp();
334 } else {
335 return os << reg.fp();
336 }
337}

339class LiftoffRegList {
340 public:
341 class Iterator;
342
343 static constexpr bool use_u16 = kAfterMaxLiftoffRegCode <= 16;
344 static constexpr bool use_u32 = !use_u16 && kAfterMaxLiftoffRegCode <= 32;
345 using storage_t = std::conditional<
346 use_u16, uint16_t,
347 std::conditional<use_u32, uint32_t, uint64_t>::type>::type;
348
349 static constexpr storage_t kGpMask =
350 storage_t{kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs.bits()};
351 static constexpr storage_t kFpMask =
352 storage_t{kLiftoffAssemblerFpCacheRegs.bits()}
353 << kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode;
354 // Sets all even numbered fp registers.
355 static constexpr uint64_t kEvenFpSetMask = uint64_t{0x5555555555555555}
356 << kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode;
357 static constexpr uint64_t kOddFpSetMask = uint64_t{0xAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA}
358 << kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode;
359
360 constexpr LiftoffRegList() = default;
361
362 // Allow to construct LiftoffRegList from a number of
363 // {Register|DoubleRegister|LiftoffRegister}.
364 template <
365 typename... Regs,
366 typename = std::enable_if_t<std::conjunction_v<std::disjunction<
367 std::is_same<Register, Regs>, std::is_same<DoubleRegister, Regs>,
368 std::is_same<LiftoffRegister, Regs>>...>>>
369 constexpr explicit LiftoffRegList(Regs... regs) {
370 (..., set(regs));
371 }
372
373 constexpr Register set(Register reg) {
374 return set(LiftoffRegister(reg)).gp();
375 }
376 constexpr DoubleRegister set(DoubleRegister reg) {
377 return set(LiftoffRegister(reg)).fp();
378 }
379
380 constexpr LiftoffRegister set(LiftoffRegister reg) {
381 if (reg.is_pair()) {
382 regs_ |= storage_t{1} << reg.low().liftoff_code();
383 regs_ |= storage_t{1} << reg.high().liftoff_code();
384 } else {
385 regs_ |= storage_t{1} << reg.liftoff_code();
386 }
387 return reg;
388 }
389
390 constexpr LiftoffRegister clear(LiftoffRegister reg) {
391 if (reg.is_pair()) {
392 regs_ &= ~(storage_t{1} << reg.low().liftoff_code());
393 regs_ &= ~(storage_t{1} << reg.high().liftoff_code());
394 } else {
395 regs_ &= ~(storage_t{1} << reg.liftoff_code());
396 }
397 return reg;
398 }
399 constexpr Register clear(Register reg) {
400 return clear(LiftoffRegister{reg}).gp();
401 }
402 constexpr DoubleRegister clear(DoubleRegister reg) {
403 return clear(LiftoffRegister{reg}).fp();
404 }
405
406 bool has(LiftoffRegister reg) const {
407 if (reg.is_pair()) {
408 DCHECK_EQ(has(reg.low()), has(reg.high()));
409 reg = reg.low();
410 }
411 return (regs_ & (storage_t{1} << reg.liftoff_code())) != 0;
412 }
413 bool has(Register reg) const { return has(LiftoffRegister{reg}); }
414 bool has(DoubleRegister reg) const { return has(LiftoffRegister{reg}); }
415
416 constexpr bool is_empty() const { return regs_ == 0; }
417
418 constexpr unsigned GetNumRegsSet() const {
419 return base::bits::CountPopulation(regs_);
420 }
421
422 constexpr LiftoffRegList operator&(const LiftoffRegList other) const {
423 return LiftoffRegList(regs_ & other.regs_);
424 }
425
426 constexpr LiftoffRegList& operator&=(const LiftoffRegList other) {
427 regs_ &= other.regs_;
428 return *this;
429 }
430
431 constexpr LiftoffRegList operator|(const LiftoffRegList other) const {
432 return LiftoffRegList(regs_ | other.regs_);
433 }
434
435 constexpr LiftoffRegList& operator|=(const LiftoffRegList other) {
436 regs_ |= other.regs_;
437 return *this;
438 }
439
440 constexpr LiftoffRegList GetAdjacentFpRegsSet() const {
441 // And regs_ with a right shifted version of itself, so reg[i] is set only
442 // if reg[i+1] is set. We only care about the even fp registers.
443 storage_t available = (regs_ >> 1) & regs_ & kEvenFpSetMask;
444 return LiftoffRegList(available);
445 }
446
447 constexpr bool HasAdjacentFpRegsSet() const {
448 return !GetAdjacentFpRegsSet().is_empty();
449 }
450
451 // Returns a list where if any part of an adjacent pair of FP regs was set,
452 // both are set in the result. For example, [1, 4] is turned into [0, 1, 4, 5]
453 // because (0, 1) and (4, 5) are adjacent pairs.
454 constexpr LiftoffRegList SpreadSetBitsToAdjacentFpRegs() const {
455 storage_t odd_regs = regs_ & kOddFpSetMask;
456 storage_t even_regs = regs_ & kEvenFpSetMask;
457 return FromBits(regs_ | ((odd_regs >> 1) & kFpMask) |
458 ((even_regs << 1) & kFpMask));
459 }
460
461 constexpr bool operator==(const LiftoffRegList other) const {
462 return regs_ == other.regs_;
463 }
464 constexpr bool operator!=(const LiftoffRegList other) const {
465 return regs_ != other.regs_;
466 }
467
468 LiftoffRegister GetFirstRegSet() const {
469 V8_ASSUME(regs_ != 0);
470 int first_code = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(regs_);
471 return LiftoffRegister::from_liftoff_code(first_code);
472 }
473
474 LiftoffRegister GetLastRegSet() const {
475 V8_ASSUME(regs_ != 0);
476 int last_code =
477 8 * sizeof(regs_) - 1 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(regs_);
478 return LiftoffRegister::from_liftoff_code(last_code);
479 }
480
481 LiftoffRegList MaskOut(const LiftoffRegList mask) const {
482 // Masking out is guaranteed to return a correct reg list, hence no checks
483 // needed.
484 return FromBits(regs_ & ~mask.regs_);
485 }
486
487 RegList GetGpList() { return RegList::FromBits(regs_ & kGpMask); }
488 DoubleRegList GetFpList() {
489 return DoubleRegList::FromBits((regs_ & kFpMask) >>
490 kAfterMaxLiftoffGpRegCode);
491 }
492
493 inline Iterator begin() const;
494 inline Iterator end() const;
495
496 static constexpr LiftoffRegList FromBits(storage_t bits) {
497 DCHECK_EQ(bits, bits & (kGpMask | kFpMask));
498 return LiftoffRegList(bits);
499 }
500
501 template <storage_t bits>
502 static constexpr LiftoffRegList FromBits() {
503 static_assert(bits == (bits & (kGpMask | kFpMask)), "illegal reg list");
504 return LiftoffRegList{bits};
505 }
506
507#if DEBUG
508 void Print() const;
509#endif
510
511 private:
512 // Unchecked constructor. Only use for valid bits.
513 explicit constexpr LiftoffRegList(storage_t bits) : regs_(bits) {}
514
515 storage_t regs_ = 0;
516};
517ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(LiftoffRegList);
518
519static constexpr LiftoffRegList kGpCacheRegList =
520 LiftoffRegList::FromBits<LiftoffRegList::kGpMask>();
521static constexpr LiftoffRegList kFpCacheRegList =
522 LiftoffRegList::FromBits<LiftoffRegList::kFpMask>();
523
524class LiftoffRegList::Iterator {
525 public:
526 LiftoffRegister operator*() { return remaining_.GetFirstRegSet(); }
527 Iterator& operator++() {
528 remaining_.clear(remaining_.GetFirstRegSet());
529 return *this;
530 }
531 bool operator==(Iterator other) { return remaining_ == other.remaining_; }
532 bool operator!=(Iterator other) { return remaining_ != other.remaining_; }
533
534 private:
535 explicit Iterator(LiftoffRegList remaining) : remaining_(remaining) {}
536 friend class LiftoffRegList;
537
538 LiftoffRegList remaining_;
539};
540
541LiftoffRegList::Iterator LiftoffRegList::begin() const {
542 return Iterator{*this};
543}
544LiftoffRegList::Iterator LiftoffRegList::end() const {
545 return Iterator{LiftoffRegList{}};
546}

548static constexpr LiftoffRegList GetCacheRegList(RegClass rc) {
549 V8_ASSUME(rc == kFpReg || rc == kGpReg);
550 static_assert(kGpReg == 0 && kFpReg == 1);
551 constexpr LiftoffRegList kRegLists[2]{kGpCacheRegList, kFpCacheRegList};
552 return kRegLists[rc];
553}
554
555inline std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, LiftoffRegList reglist) {
556 os << "{";
557 for (bool first = true; !reglist.is_empty(); first = false) {
558 LiftoffRegister reg = reglist.GetFirstRegSet();
559 reglist.clear(reg);
560 os << (first ? "" : ", ") << reg;
561 }
562 return os << "}";
563}
